  <li>The <a href="/find-help/organisation/?organisation=boaz-trust">Boaz Trust</a> night shelter provides
    temporary accommodation for men who have become homeless at some point during the asylum process (while
    waiting to access asylum support when initially making a claim; after an asylum claim has been refused;
    or when someone has been granted refugee status but have been unable to access accommodation and income
    within the narrow time frame set by the Home Office). Referrals are made online at boaztrust.org.uk/ns
    (Mon-Fri 10am-3pm).</li>
